<br>
2 hammer of the sun (read ass) to 2 clericbots, glyphed necklace to xopo and exiled necklace to someone else.<br>
<br>
Cursed...<br>
Well, no guild has ever nailed this guy on its first try and we are now no exception to that rule.  I dont think anyone got him the second time either, and no, we didnt make history that way either.  <br>
<br>
We did however settle on what seems to be a strategy that will work for us, but our execution was about as bad as it could have possibly been.  <br>
<br>
Hopefully we wont have to wait another 8 weeks to take another stab at him.  Sooner or later OC and AV will leave ssra (of course i could be wrong, fat guilds can get lazy farming the same mobs over and over and over even though they have bypassed the encounter and half the loot is not really needed), but in that event, the guilds nipping at their heels for some space in ssra (namely ody, hand and bc) should try to work out some kind of a rotation on this spawn to give everyone a chance to learn it and to keep folks from having to go months inbetween opportunitys.<br>
<br>
Well at 3am we finally decided enuf was enuf with that guy, and wouldnt ya know it, about 2 minutes after we AE TL, rhag1 pops.  The opportunity for some action (and GRC) was enticing, so not too long after he died without mercy.  No GRC dammit, Bardbot and Clericbot were forced to loot some arms they probably wont use.<br>
<br>
Rhag 2 was a lil different, we got there easy enough but due to overestimating our leetness, we didnt set up aggro properly by camping out before engaging and the bard got wasted early.  Wasted bard means the 2 clerics go oom very early and we lose.  Meanwhile the Hand had moved to AL room in anticipatoin of our band of 13 dropping rhag2... the whole time we are there acid is sending me tells &quot;how much longer&quot; etc.  Yanno, with 13 people there isnt alot of room for error and these things cannot be rushed.  Ranger saved the day (/flex) lettin a cleric get out so we rezzed up and buffed up and did it right this time, and waxed that tool.  This time at the end of the fight the clerics were FM <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
